Special instructions: Use of Face Data
- Collection of Face Data:
Our app collects facial images, which include photos or video frames containing the user’s face. Users upload these images with their explicit permission.
- Use of Collected Face Data:
The collected face data is used for personalization purposes. It enhances the user experience by providing personalized features based on facial expressions. For instance, users can generate AI dance videos by uploading their own headshot, which the app uses to create personalized dance videos.
- Sharing of Face Data:
User's facial data is not shared with any third parties. It is stored securely in our company's own database and managed internally.
- Retention of Face Data:
Face data uploaded by users is retained in our database for only one day. This retention period is for the purpose of debugging and troubleshooting generated effects. Upon user account deletion, all user-related data, including uploaded face data and generated work data, is deleted from our database.
- Storage and Security Measures:
We employ robust security measures to protect user data, including face data, stored in our database. All data is encrypted and access is strictly controlled to prevent unauthorized access.
How
          do we protect your information?
We
        implement a variety of security measures to maintain the safety of
        your personal information when you place an order or enter, submit,
        or access your personal information.
We
        offer the use of a secure server. All supplied sensitive/credit
        information is transmitted via Secure Socket Layer (SSL) technology
        and then encrypted into our Payment gateway provider's database only
        to be accessible by those authorised with special access rights to
        such systems, and are required to keep the information confidential.
Do
          we use cookies?
No,
        our product does use cookies.
Do
          we disclose any information to outside parties?
We
        do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer to outside parties your
        personally identifiable information. This does not include trusted
        third parties who assist us in operating our website, conducting our
        business, or servicing you, so long as those parties agree to keep
        this information confidential. We may also release your information
        when we believe release is appropriate to comply with the law,
        enforce our site policies, or protect ours or others' rights,
        property, or safety. However, non-personally identifiable visitor
        information may be provided to other parties for marketing,
        advertising, or other uses.
